.TH "upper_size_to_lower_size" 9 "upper_size_to_lower_size" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
upper_size_to_lower_size \- 
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "loff_t" upper_size_to_lower_size
.BI "(struct ecryptfs_crypt_stat *crypt_stat "  ","
.BI "loff_t upper_size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "crypt_stat" 12
Crypt_stat associated with file
.IP "upper_size" 12
Size of the upper file
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Calculate the required size of the lower file based on the
specified size of the upper file. This calculation is based on the
number of headers in the underlying file and the extent size.

Returns Calculated size of the lower file.
